nt%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EA%20video%20has%20surfaced%20on%20various%20social%20media%20platforms%20that%20reportedly%20shows%20Russian%20soldiers%20executing%20three%20Ukrainian%20troops%20who%20were%20captured%20in%20the%20Zaporizhzhia%20region%20during%20the%20ongoing%20war.%20The%20video%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.me%2Fhromadske_ua%2F40942%5C%22%3Efirst%20posted%20on%20Telegram%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Wednesday%20and%20later%20appeared%20on%20social%20media%2C%20where%20it%20was%20shared%20by%20many%20journalists.%20The%20clip%20shows%20the%20three%20soldiers%2C%20kneeling%20with%20their%20hands%20behind%20their%20heads%2C%20being%20shot%20by%20their%20captives.%20As%20the%20video%20gained%20traction%2C%20Ukraine's%20Prosecutor%20General's%20Office%20launched%20an%20investigation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20they%20shoot%20the%20%26quot%3BPrisoners%20of%20War%20(POWs)%26quot%3B%2C%20smoke%20is%20seen%20emerging%20from%20the%20weapon%20purportedly%20held%20by%20Russian%20soldiers%20before%20the%20men%20collapse%20to%20the%20ground.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeveral%20news%20outlets%20in%20Ukraine%20have%20condemned%20the%20incident%20saying%20it%20shows%20how%20Vladimir%20Putin's%20forces%20%26quot%3Bare%20simply%20not%20human%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20statement%20from%20Prosecutor%20General's%20Office%20in%20Kyiv%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BThe%20Russian%20army%20captured%20three%20Ukrainian%20defenders%20during%20a%20combat%20clash%20near%20the%20village%20of%20Robotyne%2C%20Zaporizhzhia%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAn%20hour%20later%2C%20in%20violation%20of%20Article%203%20of%20the%20Geneva%20Convention%20on%20the%20Treatment%20of%20Prisoners%20of%20War%2C%20the%20occupiers%20shot%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20added.%3Cbr%3E%5CnThe%20office%20informed%20that%20the%20investigation%20is%20being%20carried%20out%20by%20the%20SBU%20Department%2C%20Ukraine's%20intelligence%20service.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENo%20official%20Ukrainian%20authority%20has%20reacted%20t