rst%20half%20hour%20of%20play.%20Two%20bowlers%20they%20started%20with%2C%20that%20tactically%20was%20a%20big%20mistake.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFormer%20India%20player%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Sanjay%20Manjrekar%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsports.ndtv.com%2Fcricket%2Fplayers%2F41124-sanjay-vijay-manjrekar-playerprofile%5C%22%3ESanjay%20Manjrekar%3C%2Fa%3E%20agreed%20with%20Ravi%20Shastri's%20opinion.%C2%A0%26quot%3BClearly%20India%20missed%20the%20trick.%20This%20is%20something%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Rahul%20Dravid%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsports.ndtv.com%2Fcricket%2Fplayers%2F174-rahul-dravid-playerprofile%5C%22%3ERahul%20Dravid%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20Rohit%20Sharma%20must%20have%20thought%20about%20during%20the%20break%20and%20then%20decided%20to%20go%20with%20Prasidh%20and%20Shardul.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFormer%20South%20Africa%20pacer%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Vernon%20Philander%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsports.ndtv.com%2Fcricket%2Fplayers%2F894-vernon-philander-playerprofile%5C%22%3EVernon%20Philander%3C%2Fa%3E%20felt%20that%20the%20strategy%20might%20have%20been%20used%20to%20keep%20Jasprit%20Bumrah.%20%26quot%3BPerhaps%20they%20wanted%20to%20preserve%20him%20(Bumrah)%20after%20the%206-over%20spell%20he%20bowled%20(before%20lunch).%20I%20think%20it's%20a%20window%20of%20opportunity%20that%20India%20lost.%20India%20gave%20away%20%C2%A042%20runs%20and%20that%20gave%20South%20Africa%20the%20momentum%20after%20lunch.%20They%20lost%20an%20opportunity%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOn%20any%20pecking%20order%2C%20these%20two%20(Shardul%20and%20Prasidh)%20would%20have%20been%20the%20last%20to%20start%20the%20proceedings%20(after%20lunch)%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Shastri%20on%20commentary.%20The%20former%20India%20all-rounder%20seemed%20bemused%20and%20a%20tad%20irritated%20by%20India's%20tactics.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20something%20that%20we've%20had%20a%20discussion%20multiple%20times%20when%20I%20was%20the%20coach.%20And%20more%20often%20than%20not%20we%20decided%20to%20go%20with%20the%20best%20two%20bowlers%20at%20the%20start%20of%20the%20session.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20cast%20your%20mind%20back%2C%20India%20would%20feel%20they%20have%20missed%20a%20massive%20trick%20in%20the%20first%20half%20hour%20of%20play.%20Two%20bowlers%20they%20started%20with%20that%20tactically%20was%20a%20big%20mistake%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20emphasized.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConcurring%20with%20Shastri%2C%20Manjrekar%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BClearly%20India%20missed%20the%20trick.%20This%20is%20something%20Rahul%20Dravid%20and%20Rohit%20Sharma%20must%20have%20thought%20about%20during%20the%20break%20and%20then%20decided%20to%20go%20with%3Cbr%3E%5CnPrasidh%20and%20Shardul.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFormer%20South%20Africa%20pacer%20Vernon%20Philander%20tried%20to%20think%20of%20a%20reason%20behind%20the%20strategy%20and%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BPerhaps%20they%20wanted%20to%20preserve%20him%20(Bumrah)%20after%20the%206-over%20spell%20he%20bowled%20(before%20lunch).%20I%20think%20it's%20a%20window%20of%20opportunity%20that%20India%20lost.%20India%20gave%20away%20%C2%A042%20runs%20and%20that%20gave%20South%20Africa%20the%20momentum%20after%20lunch.%20They%20lost%20an%20opportunity.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20time%20of%20Stumps%2C%20South%20Africa's%20score%20read%20256%2F5%20-lead%20by%2011%20runs-%20with%20Elgar%20(140)%20and%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Marco%20Jansen%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsports.ndtv.com%2Fcricket%2Fplayers%2F113406-marco-jansen-playerprofile%5C%22%3EMarco%20Jansen%3C%2Fa%3E%20(3)%20unbeaten%20at%20the%20crease.%20Runs%20flowed%20from%20the%20bats%20of%20Elgar%20and%20David%20Bedingham%2C%20but%20India%20made%20crucial%20breakthroughs%20before%20bad%20light%20cut%20play%20short.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20last%20session%20of%20the%20day%20started%20with%20the%20debutant%20David%20Bedingham%20slamming%20a%20half-century%20while%20rotating%20the