ed%20from%20the%20hospital%20on%20the%20same%20day.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22esnodgrass%40insider.com%20(Erin%20Snodgrass)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A7%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcruise-passengers-hospitalized-after-chartered-flight-hits-turbulence-2023-12%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22YouTube%20made%20%24959%20million%20in%20ad%20revenue%20off%20children%20last%20year%2C%20followed%20closely%20by%20Instagram%3A%20Harvard%20study%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22the%20logos%20of%20Facebook%2C%20YouTube%2C%20TikTok%20and%20Snapchat%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F658cc2791c5c7b8c9a0c6d58%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAccording%20to%20the%20Harvard%20study%2C%20YouTube%20derived%20the%20greatest%20ad%20revenue%20from%20users%2012%20and%20under%20(%24959.1%20million)%2C%20followed%20by%20Instagram%20(%24801.1%20million)%20and%20Facebook%20(%24137.2%20million).%3Cp%3E(AP%20Photo%2C%20File)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ESocial%20media%20companies%20made%20more%20than%20%2411%20billion%20in%20US%20ad%20revenue%20from%20kids%2C%20a%20new%20study%20found.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20study%20suggests%20the%20are%20too%20many%20financial%20incentives%20at%20play%20for%20the%20companies%20to%20take%20meaningful%20action.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EYouTube%20derived%20the%20greatest%20ad%20revenue%20from%20users%2012%20and%20under%2C%20according%20to%20the%20study.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ESocial%20media%20companies%20collectively%20made%20over%20%2411%20billion%20in%20US%20advertising%20revenue%20from%20minors%20last%20year%2C%20according%20to%20a%20study%20from%20the%20Harvard%20T.H.%20Chan%20School%20of%20Public%20Health%20published%20on%20Wednesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20researchers%20say%20the%20findings%20show%20a%20need%20for%20government%20regulation%20of%20social%20media%20since%20the%20companies%20that%20stand%20to%20make%20money%20from%20children%20who%20use%20their%20platforms%20have%20failed%20to%20meaningfully%20self-regulate.%20They%20note%20such%20regulations%2C%20as%20well%20as%20greater%20transparency%20from%20tech%20companies%2C%20could%20help%20alleviate%20harms%20to%20youth%20mental%20health%20and%20curtail%20potentially%20harmful%20advertising%20practices%20that%20target%20children%20and%20adolescents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20come%20up%20with%20the%20revenue%20figure%2C%20the%20researchers%20estimated%20the%20number%20of%20users%20under%2018%20on%20Facebook%2C%20Instagram%2C%20Snapchat%2C%20TikTok%2C%20X%20(formerly%20Twitter)%20and%20YouTube%20in%202022%20based%20on%20population%20data%20from%20the%20U.S.%20Census%20and%20survey%20data%20from%20Common%20Sense%20Media%20and%20Pew%20Research.%20They%20then%20used%20data%20from%20research%20firm%20eMarketer%2C%20now%20called%20Insider%20Intelligence%2C%20and%20Qustodio%2C%20a%20parental%20control%20app%2C%20to%20estimate%20each%20platform's%20U.S.%20ad%20revenue%20in%202022%20and%20the%20time%20children%20spent%20per%20day%20on%20each%20platform.%20After%20that%2C%20the%20researchers%20said%20they%20built%20a%20simulation%20model%20using%20the%20data%20to%20estimate%20how%20much%20ad%20revenue%20the%20platforms%20earned%20from%20minors%20in%20the%20U.S.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResearchers%20and%20lawmakers%20have%20long%20focused%20on%20the%20negative%20effects%20stemming%20from%20social%20media%20platforms%2C%20whose%20personally-tailored%20algorithms%20can%20drive%20children%20towards%20excessive%20use.%20This%20year%2C%20lawmakers%20in%20states%20like%20New%20York%20and%20Utah%20introduced%20or%20passed%20legislation%20that%20would%20curb%20social%20media%20use%20among%20kids%2C%20citing%20harms%20to%20youth%20mental%20health%20and%20other%20concerns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeta%2C%20which%20owns%20Instagram%20and%20Facebook%2C%20is%20also%20being%20sued%20by%20dozens%20of%20states%20for%20allegedly%20contributing%20to%20the%20mental%20health%20crisis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAlthough%20social%20media%20platforms%20may%20claim%20that%20they%20can%20self-regulate%20their%20practices%20to%20reduce%20the%20harms%20to%20young%20people%2C%20they%20have%20yet%20to%20do%20so%2C%20and%20our%20study%20suggests%20they%20have%20overwhelming%20financial%20incentives%20to%20continue%20to%20delay%20taking%20meaningful%20steps%20to%20protect%20children%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Bryn%20Austin%2C%20a%20professor%20in%20the%20Department%20of%20Social%20and%20Behavioral%20Sciences%20at%20Harvard%20and%20a%20senior%20author%20on%20the%20study.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20platforms%20themselves%20don't%20make%20public%20how%20much%20money%20they%20earn%20from%20minors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYouTube%20especially%20has%20become%20hugely%20popular%20with%20young%20children%2C%20who%20generally%20prefer%20the%20platform%20to%20other%20major%20streaming%20services%20like%20Netflix.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMichael%20Hirsh%2C%20animator%20and%20co-founder%20of%20WOW%20Unlimited%20Media%2C%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Fbusiness%2Fmedia%2Fyour-kid-prefers-youtube-to-netflix-thats-a-problem-for-streamers-86b132f8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20kids%20are%20being%20drawn%20more%20and%20more%20to%20shorter%20content%20as%20opposed%20to%20traditional%20length%20shows.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20viewers%20are%20watching%20on%20their%20iPads%20or%20on%20other%20platforms%20that%20have%20moved%20to%20shorter%20and%20shorter%20segments%2C%20and%20it's%20a%20real%20issue%20for%20the%20streamers%2C%26quot%3B%20Hirsh%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F10%2F10%2Fstyle%2Fchildren-influencers-money.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EYouTube%20content%20tailored%20to%20kids%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20also%20drawing%20in%20big%20bucks%20for%20the%2