s.%20The%20aid%2C%20provided%20through%20the%20Presidential%20Drawdown%20Authority%2C%20will%20be%20pulled%20from%20Pentagon%20stockpiles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%2C%20Marine%20Lt.%20Col.%20Garron%20Garn%2C%20a%20Pentagon%20spokesman%20said%20there%20is%20no%20more%20funding%20to%20replace%20the%20weapons%20taken%20from%20department%20stocks.%20And%20the%20Ukraine%20Security%20Assistance%20Initiative%2C%20which%20provides%20long-term%20funding%20for%20future%20weapons%20contracts%2C%20is%20also%20out%20of%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20Garn%20said%20Wednesday%2C%20%26quot%3BWithout%20the%20supplemental%20funding%2C%20there%20will%20be%20a%20shortfall%20in%20replenishing%20U.S.%20military%20stocks%2C%20affecting%20American%20military%20readiness.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPresident%20Joe%20Biden%20is%20urging%20Congress%20to%20pass%20a%20%24110%20billion%20aid%20package%20for%20Ukraine%2C%20Israel%20and%20other%20national%20security%20needs.%20It%20includes%20%2461.4%20billion%20for%20Ukraine%2C%20with%20about%20half%20to%20replenish%20Pentagon%20stocks.%20It%20also%20includes%20about%20%2414%20billion%20for%20Israel%20as%20it%20fights%20Hamas%20and%20%2414%20billion%20for%20U.S.%20border%20security.%20Other%20funds%20would%20go%20for%20security%20needs%20in%20the%20Asia-Pacific.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDue%20to%20an%20accounting%20error%20that%20overvalued%20some%20of%20the%20weapons%20sent%20to%20Ukraine%20over%20the%20past%20year%20or%20more%2C%20there%20is%20still%20about%20%244.2%20billion%20in%20restored%20drawdown%20authority.%20But%20since%20the%20Pentagon%20has%20no%20money%20to%20replenish%20inventory%20sent%20to%20Kyiv%2C%20the%20department%20will%20have%20to%20%26quot%3Brigorously%20assess%26quot%3B%20any%20future%20aid%20and%20its%20implications%20on%20the%20U.S.%20military's%20ability%20to%20protect%20America%2C%20Garn%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20the%2054th%20tranche%20of%20military%20aid%20taken%20from%20department%20shelves%2