0Mahmood%20Madani%2C%20has%20conveyed%20his%20concerns%20to%20the%20prime%20minister%20and%20home%20minister%2C%20highlighting%20the%20potential%20harm%20to%20the%20'shared%20cultural%20heritage'.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A20%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fndmc-considers-demolition-of-delhis-sunehri-masjid-jamiat-ulama-i-hind-objects%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22In%20the%20US's%20Pannun%20Murder%20Plot%20Indictment%2C%20the%20Devil%20for%20the%20Modi%20Government%20Lies%20In%20the%20Dates%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F30010249%2Findictment.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20alleged%20plot%20to%20murder%20a%20United%20States%20citizen%2C%20Gurpatwant%20Singh%20Pannun%2C%20on%20US%20soil%20is%20a%20much%20more%20serious%20matter%20than%20India%E2%80%99s%20government%20and%20some%20commentators%20have%20claimed.%20This%20becomes%20clear%20from%20a%20careful%20reading%20of%20the%20US%20Justice%20Department%E2%80%99s%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.justice.gov%2Fd9%2F2023-11%2Fu.s._v._gupta_indictment.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ecriminal%20indictment%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20The%20crucial%20details%20are%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Edates%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20listed%20in%20that%20document.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPrime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20had%20been%20accorded%20a%20state%20visit%20%E2%80%93%20the%20highest%20honour%20that%20the%20Americans%20can%20confer%20on%20a%20foreign%20leader.%20That%20brought%20him%20to%20the%20US%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fmodis-us-visit-subject-defence-analysis%5C%22%3Ebetween%20June%2021%20and%2023%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20key%20day%20was%20the%2022nd.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20began%20with%20a%20meeting%20in%20the%20Oval%20Office%20with%20President%20Joe%20Biden.%20Modi%20then%20addressed%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mea.gov.in%2FSpeeches-Statements.htm%3Fdtl%2F36714%2FAddress_by_Prime_Minister_Shri_Narendra_Modi_to_the_Joint_Session_of_the_US_Congress%5C%22%3Ejoint%20session%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20United%20States%20Congress%2C%20and%20that%20evening%20a%20glittering%20state%20dinner%20in%20his%20honour%20was%20held%20at%20the%20White%20House.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhere%20the%20indictment%20speaks%20of%20%E2%80%9Cengagements%E2%80%9D%20between%20%E2%80%9Chigh-level%20US%20and%20Indian%20government%20officials%E2%80%9D%2C%20this%20is%20clearly%20a%20reference%20to%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20state%20visit.%20The%20officials%20in%20India%20whom%20the%20indictment%20states%20were%20allegedly%20guiding%20the%20assassination%20plot%20through%20%E2%80%98Nick%E2%80%99%20at%20first%20urged%20that%20no%20action%20be%20taken%20during%20these%20%E2%80%9Cengagements%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20then%20for%20some%20reason%20that%20instruction%20was%20changed.%20The%20plot%E2%80%99s%20authors%20in%20Delhi%2C%20according%20to%20the%20indictment%2C%20were%20eventually%20prepared%20for%20the%20killing%20to%20take%20place%20during%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20visit.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20June%2019%2C%20Nikhil%20Gupta%20%E2%80%93%20the%20alleged%20organiser%20of%20the%20murder%20%E2%80%93%20told%20the%20person%20he%20thought%20was%20a%20hit%20man%20(who%20was%20actually%20a%20US%20government%20agent%20operating%20under%20cover)%20that%20in%20light%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fterrorism-accused-hardeep-singh-nijjar-shot-to-death-in-surrey-bc-gurdwara%5C%22%3Ethe%20killing%20the%20previous%20day%20of%20a%20Sikh%20secessionist%20in%20Canada%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20there%20was%20%E2%80%9Cnow%20no%20need%20to%20wait%E2%80%9D%20to%20assassinate%20Pannun%20in%20New%20York.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20June%2020t%2C%20Gupta%E2%80%99s%20alleged%20handlers%20in%20India%20told%20him%20that%20the%20murder%20of%20Pannun%20was%20now%20a%20%E2%80%9Cpriority%E2%80%9D.%20On%20that%20day%2C%20Gupta%20passed%20on%20the%20message%3A%20%E2%80%9Cwe%20got%20the%20go-ahead%20to%20go%20anytime%2C%20even%20today%2C%20tomorrow%2C%20as%20early%20as%20possible%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CTomorrow%E2%80%9D%20was%20June%2021%2C%20the%20day%20that%20Modi%20arrived%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%20%7C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fnikhil-gupta-pannun-assassination-plot-documents%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Nick%E2%80%99%2C%20a%20Money%20Courier%20and%20a%20Hitman%3A%20What%20New%20Documents%20Say%20About%20The%20Pannun%20Murder%20Plot%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20June%2022%2C%20the%20day%20of%20the%20prime%20minister%E2%80%99s%20address%20to%20Congress%20and%20the%20state%20dinner%2C%20Gupta%E2%80%99s%20alleged%20contact%20in%20New%20Delhi%20told%20him%20that%20he%20had%20received%20a%20message%20from%20the%20%E2%80%9Cboss%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20that%20if%20the%20hit%20man%20could%20confim%20that%20the%20victim%20was%20at%20home%2C%20%E2%80%9Cit%20will%20be%20a%20go%20ahead%20from%20us%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20astonishing%20that%20this%20assassination%20could%20have%20been%20contemplated%20on%20the%20day%20that%20Modi%20addressed%20the%20US%20Congress%20and%20was%20being%20honoured%20at%20a%20state%20dinner.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20indictment%20alleges%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Cgo%20ahead%E2%80%9D%20came%20from%20Gupta%E2%80%99s%20superiors%20in%20India.%20The%20clear%20implication%20is%20that%20he%20was%20not%20a%20lone%2C%20rogue%20actor.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20indictment%20speaks%20of%20a%20video%20meeting%20allegedly%20linked%20to%20the%20plot%20in%20a%20conference%20room%20in%20New%20Delhi%20with%20%E2%80%9Capproximately%20three%20other%20men%20in%20the%20room%20who%20were%20dressed%20in%20business%20attire%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20clear%20implication%20is%20that%20they%20were%20officials%2C%20possibly%20in%20an%20intelligence%20or%20security%20agency.%20They%20appear%20to%20have%20had%20their%20own%20operatives%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20messages%20to%20Gupta%20%E2%80%93%20noted%20in%20the%20indictment%20%E2%80%93%20indicate%20that%20his%20handlers%20for%20this%20operation%20had%20informants%20on%20the%20ground%20who%20were%20providing%20him%20with%20additional%20information%20on%20the%20intended%20victim.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20indictment%20also%20includes%20taped%20references%20by%20Gupta%20and%20his%20handler%2C%20CC-1%2C%20in%20which%20the%20latter%20refers%20to%20the%20%E2%80%9Cboss%E2%80%9D%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20title%3D%5C%22Page%2011%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CAt%20one%20point%2C%20on%20or%20about%20June%2022%2C%202023%2C%20CC-1%20messaged%20GUPTA%20that%20the%20Victim%20%E2%80%9Cis%20somewhere%20else%2C%E2%80%9D%20that%20%E2%80%9C%5Bh%5De%20is%20not%20at%20home%2C%E2%80%9D%20and%20that%20CC-1%20%E2%80%9Cgot%20the%20message%20from%20boss.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20boss%E2%80%99s%20identity%20is%20not%20revealed%20in%20the%20indictment.%20We%20do%20not%20know%20if%C2%A0%20the%20Americans%20%E2%80%93%20who%20know%20the%20identity%20of%20CC-1%2C%20Gupta%E2%80%99s%20immediate%20contact%20in%20India%C2%A0%20%E2%80%93%20are%20aware%20of%20who%20the%20%E2%80%98boss%E2%80%99%20is.%20But%20the%20evidence%20in%20the%20indictment%20suggests%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Cboss%E2%80%9D%20is%20likely%20to%20have%20been%20a%20senior%20official%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20security%20establishment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EGiven%20the%20extremely%20over-centralised%20nature%20of%20the%20Modi%20government%2C%20it%20seems%20unlikely%20that%20this%20murder%20plot%20could%20have%20been%20planned%20without%20the%20knowledge%20of%20individuals%20very%20close%20to%20the%20prime%20minister.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FTaHMOZe_GFw%3Fsi%3DUHrPLZpAuC2l_4LQ%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20could%20create%20excruciating%20problems%20for%20the%20Indian%20authorities.%20They%20may%20need%20to%20consider%20how%20to%20treat%20a%20leading%20figure%20in%20the%20security%20services%2C%20and%20possibly%20even%20a%20senior%20political%20leader%20%E2%80%93%20with%20a%20national%20election%20looming.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EGiven%20the%20supposed%20importance%20to%20New%20Delhi%20of%20US-Indian%20relations%2C%20it%20is%20remarkable%20that%20a%20murder%20of%20an%20American%20citizen%20on%20US%20soil%20could%20have%20been%20contemplated%20at%20all%20%E2%80%93%20and%20that%2C%20as%20the%20indictment%20alleges%20with%20supporting%20evidence%2C%20other%20victims%20could%20also%20have%20been%20intended.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20the%20fact%20that%20this%20attack%20on%20Pannun%20could%20have%20occurred%20during%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20state%20visit%20to%20the%20US%20borders%20on%20political%20insanity.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Biden%20government%20has%20so%20far%20been%20willing%20to%20overlook%20abundant%20evidence%20supplied%20to%20it%20of%20numerous%20startling%20outrages%20by%20the%20Modi%20government%20and%20its%20allies%20within%20India.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EThese%20include%20attacks%20on%20the%20media%20which%20persuaded%20Reporters%20Without%20Borders%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Frsf-narendra-modi-press-freedom-predators-kim-jongun-imran-khan-vladimir-putin%5C%22%3Eto%20identify%20Modi%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Cpredator%E2%80%9D%20of%20media%20freedom%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20repressive%20actions%20against%20civil%20society%20which%20even%20targeted%20two%20Nobel%20Peace%20Prize%20winners%3A%20Amnesty%20International%20and%20Mother%20Teresa%E2%80%99s%20Missionaries%20of%20Charity.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EGiven%20Biden%E2%80%99s%20apparent%20indifference%20to%20these%20issues%2C%20Indian%20leaders%20appear%2C%20astoundingly%2C%20to%20have%20believed%20that%20they%20could%20also%20get%20away%20with%20a%20murder%20of%20an%20American%20on%20US%20soil.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThey%20were%20mistaken.%20This%20is%20a%20deeply%20serious%20matter.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fjames-manor%2F%5C%22%3EJames%20Manor%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20emeritus%20professor%20of%20commonwealth%20studies%20in%20the%20School%20of%20Advanced%20Study%2C%20University%20of%20London.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703668290000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F30010249%2Findictment.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fin-the-uss-pannun-murder-plot-indictment-the-devil-for-the-modi-government-lies-in-the-dates%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20fact%20that%20Nikhil%20Gupta's%20alleged%20handlers%20in%20India%20told%20him%20they%20had%20the%20%E2%80%98go-ahead%E2%80%99%20to%20murder%20Pannun%20as%20early%20as%20June%2021%2C%20the%20date%20of%20Modi's%20arrival%20in%20the%20US%2C%20borders%20on%20political%20insanity.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A6%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fin-the-uss-pannun-murder-plot-indictment-the-devil-for-the-modi-government-lies-in-the-dates%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20Wire%20Recommends%3A%20Eight%20Movies%20We%20Watched%20and%20Liked%20This%20Year%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F26165932%2Fmovies.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E1.%20Ajoy%20Ashirwad%20Mahaprashasta%3A%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Worst%20Person%20in%20The%20World%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Norwegian%20auteur%20Joachim%20Trier%E2%80%99s%20third%20film%20of%20his%20Oslo%20Trilogy%2C%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Worst%20Person%20in%20The%20World%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20was%20one%20of%20the%20best%20immersive%20experiences%20I%20have%20had%20in%20a%20long%20time.%20Trier%20takes%20us%20through%20melancholy%20and%20a%20deep%20sense%20of%20alienation%20in%20metropolitan%20life%2C%20all%20through%20the%20remarkably%20realistic%20story%20of%20Julie%2C%20an%20Oslo-based%20medical%20student%20in%20her%2020s.%20Julie%20is%20independent%2C%20creative%2C%20experimental%20and%20evades%20walking%20the%20conventional%20route%20almost%20compulsively.%20That%20makes%20her%20uncertain%20at%20almost%20all%20times%2C%20even%20guilty%20of%20her%20unorthodoxy%2C%20but%20still%20determined%20enough%20to%20arrest%20cynicism.%20A%20cinematic%20masterpiece.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%20Sravasti%20Dasgupta%3A%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Banshees%20of%20Inisherin%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20Irish%20tragi-comedy%20came%20to%20my%20notice%20during%20this%20year%E2%80%99s%20Oscar%20season.%20But%20in%20all%20honesty%20nothing%20could%20have%20prepared%20me%20for%20this%20gripping%20tale%20of%20friendship%2C%20loss%20and%20the%20intersection%20of%20culture%20and%20politics%20served%20in%20a%20narrative%20style%20that%20I%20have%20never%20seen%20or%20experienced%20before.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESet%20in%20the%20backdrop%20of%20the%20Irish%20War%20of%20Independence%2C%20the%20movie%20on%20its%20surface%20tells%20the%20story%20of%20a%20feud%20between%20two%20close%20friends%20while%20serving%20as%20a%20metaphor%20for%20the%20waning%20Irish%20nation%2C%20its%20people%2C%20their%20aspirations%20and%20the%20innate%20human%20need%20to%20be%20remembered.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%E2%80%99s%20funny%2C%20sad%2C%20poignant%20but%20most%20importantly%20it%20is%20very%20enjoyable%2C%20will%20keep%20you%20hooked%20through%20its%20running%20time%20and%20will%20remain%20in%20your%20thoughts%20well%20after%20its%20over!%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20Soumashree%20Sarkar%3A%20%3Cem%3EDecision%20to%20Leave%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Park%20Chanwook%2C%20Korean%2C%202022%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20blue%20and%20brown%20%E2%80%93%20the%20colours%20of%20the%20sky%20and%20the%20earth%20%E2%80%93%20can%20melt%20into%20each%20other%20so%20seamlessly%20and%20yet%20give%20the%20viewer%20a%20sense%20of%20menace%20is%20something%20this%20film%20teaches%20you.%20It%20marries%20a%20powerful%20plot%20to%20the%20plot%E2%80%99s%20own%20powerlessness%20when%20faced%20with%20a%20rather%20debilitating%20sort%20of%20a%20love%20story.%20You%20are%20left%20with%20a%20sense%20of%20having%20delved%20into%20a%20secret.%20Park%20Haeil%20is%20a%20noted%20actor%2C%20a%20man%20of%20many%20on-screen%20success%2C%20but%20the%20hero%20of%20the%20film%20is%20Tang%20Wei%2C%20who%20speaks%20without%20speaking%20and%20conveys%20emotions%20without%20artifice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E4.%20Anirudh%20S.K.%3A%20%3Cem%3ENaduvula%20Konjam%20Pakkatha%20Kaanom%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20liked%20the%20Tamil%20comedy%20movie%20%3Cem%3ENaduvula%20Konjam%20Pakkatha%20Kaanom%3C%2Fem%3E.%20It%20means%20%E2%80%98Some%20pages%20from%20the%20middle%20are%20missing%E2%80%99.%20It%E2%80%99s%20about%20a%20guy%20who%20gets%20short-term%20memory%20loss%20before%20his%20wedding%20and%20how%20his%20friends%20help%20him%20keep%20it%20under%20wraps.%20Even%20though%20I%20struggled%20with%20the%20language%2C%20I%20was%20able%20to%20understand%20the%20film%E2%80%99s%20wholesome%20humour%2C%20which%20was%20great.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E5.%20Seema%20Chishti%3A%20Podcasts%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20far%20as%20audio-visuals%20go%2C%20not%20films%20but%20audio%20had%20me%20hooked.%20This%20was%20the%20one%20year%2C%20other%20than%20the%20pandemic%20year%20of%202020%2C%20when%20podcasts%20spoke%20to%20me.%20The%20now%20discontinued%20scintillating%20%3Cem%3ESinica%3C%2Fem%3E%20podcast%2C%20and%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Rest%20is%20Politics%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20%3Cem%3EEmpire%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20each%20of%20these%20would%20make%20my%20day%20each%20time%20a%20new%20episode%20popped%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E6.%20Faiyaz%20Ahmad%20Wajeeh%3A%20%3Cem%3EWhile%20We%20Watched%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWatching%20%3Cem%3EWhile%20We%20Watched%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20a%20documentary%20about%20veteran%20journalist%20Ravish%20Kumar%2C%20may%20be%20a%20tough%20and%20painful%20experience%2C%20but%20it%20gives%20a%20new%20perspective%20on%20what%20journalism%20really%20means%20in%20these%20dark%20times%20for%20Indian%20TV%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20documentary%20narrates%20the%20tale%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20deteriorating%20democratic%20framework%20and%20how%20the%20media%20has%20turned%20away%20from%20journalism%20on%20all%20the%20fundamental%20issues%20and%20important%20questions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20explains%20how%20journalism%20is%20not%20about%20associating%20yourself%20with%20a%20sponsored%20opinion%20or%20propaganda%2C%20but%20about%20speaking%20the%20truth%20even%20when%20there%20is%20no%20one%20to%20listen%20to%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20words%2C%20%3Cem%3EWhile%20We%20Watched%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20the%20war%20cry%20of%20an%20unarmed%20journalist%20fighting%20for%20democracy%20on%20the%20battlefield.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E7.%20Sangeeta%20Barooah%20Pisharoty%3A%20%3Cem%3EMunich%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20horrible%20Israel-Hamas%20conflict%20unfolding%2C%20Netflix%20threw%20at%20its%20viewers%20a%20litany%20of%20films%2C%20famous%20or%20otherwise%2C%20which%20have%20dealt%20with%20the%20bloody%20history%20of%20the%20Israel-Palestine%20question.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20re-watched%20%3Cem%3EMunich%3C%2Fem%3E.%20It%20not%20only%20helped%20refresh%20a%20ghastly%20episode%20from%20that%20long-drawn-out%20conflict%20in%20West%20Asia%20where%20so%20many%20innocent%20lives%20have%20been%20lost%20over%20the%20decades%2C%20but%20also%20facilitated%20making%20two%20other%20observations%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3Ea)%20on%20a%20tiny%20nation%E2%80%99s%20resolve%20to%20hunt%20down%20its%20perpetrators%20and%20meticulously%20executing%20it%20using%20first-rate%20espionage%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3Eb)%20and%2C%20that%20the%20journey%20that%20began%20then%20ultimately%20made%20Israel%20forever%20hinged%20on%20victimhood.%20It%20is%20today%20abhorred%20not%20just%20by%20the%20Palestinians%20for%20being%20their%20perpetrator%20but%20also%20helped%20craft%20for%20itself%20the%20dubious%20perception%20worldwide%20that%20it%20peddles%20marketers%20of%20%E2%80%98spy%20hood%E2%80%99%20to%20surveillance%20states%20to%20be%20able%20to%20hunt%20anyone%20and%20everyone%20that%20those%20regimes%20count%20as%20their%20%E2%80%98enemies%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E8.%20Jahnavi%20Sen%3A%20%3Cem%3EMast%20Mein%20Rehne%20Ka%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20came%20across%20this%20playful-but-poignant%20movie%20by%20accident%2C%20and%2C%20having%20gone%20in%20with%20no%20expectations%2C%20was%20very%20pleasantly%20surprised.%20Jackie%20Shroff%20and%20Neena%20Gupta%20portray%20two%20elderly%20people%20living%20their%20loneliness%20in%20very%20different%20ways%2C%20and%20their%20unlikely%20friendship%20%E2%80%93%20as%20well%20as%20the%20stellar%20acting%20by%20Abhishek%20Chauhan%20%E2%80%93%20make%20for%20a%20warm%2C%20sometimes%20sad%2C%20and%20thought-provoking%20watch.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703665847000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F26165932%2Fmovies.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Fthe-wire-recommends-movies%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22As%20the%20year%20comes%20to%20a%20close%2C%20The%20Wire's%20staff%20looks%20back%20on%20some%20of%20the%20films%20they%20watched%20they%20year%20that%20have%20stayed%20with%20them.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Fthe-wire-recommends-movies%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%E2%80%98Kho%20Gaye%20Hum%20Kahan%E2%80%99%20Starts%20Strong%2C%20But%20Settles%20For%20the%20Recall%20Value%20of%20An%20Insta%20Reel%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F27120951%2Fimage-1675.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20premise%20of%20three%20friends%20coming%20of%20age%20in%20an%20Excel%20Entertainment%20film%2C%20is%20almost%20a%20ritual%20for%20Hindi%20film%20fans%20every%20few%20years.%20The%20production%20house%20burst%20onto%20the%20scene%20with%20%3Cem%3EDil%20Chahta%20Hai%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2001)%20%E2%80%93%20following%20three%20friends%20from%20their%20early%2020s%20to%20their%20late%2020s%3B%20and%20then%20followed%20it%20up%20with%20%3Cem%3EZindagi%20Na%20Milegi%20Dobara%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2011)%2C%20which%20was%20set%20around%20three%20childhood%20friends%20making%20good%20on%20a%20college%20pact%20in%20their%2030s.%20In%202023%2C%20the%20production%20house%2C%20coupled%20with%20Zoya%20Akhtar%20and%20Reema%20Kagti%E2%80%99s%20Tiger%20Baby%20Films%2C%20tells%20a%20tale%20of%20three%20friends%20navigating%20their%20double%20lives%20in%20the%20social%20media%20era.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20movies%20are%20usually%20set%20in%20an%20upper-middle%20class%20neighbourhood%2C%20amongst%20those%20not%20struggling%20for%20their%20basic%20needs.%20There%E2%80%99s%20a%20relaxed%20vibe%20in%20these%20films%2C%20as%20an%20eclectic%20group%20of%20musicians%20make%20up%20the%20film%E2%80%99s%20soundtrack%20to%20play%20through%20montages%2C%20and%20characters%20try%20to%20find%20out%20what%20it%20all%20really%20means.%20Both%20Farhan%20Akhtar%E2%80%99s%20film%20and%20Zoya%20Akhtar%E2%80%99s%20film%20conclude%20with%20life-altering%20epiphanies%3A%20some%20friendships%20survive%20everything%2C%20or%20how%20road%20trips%20can%20bring%20catharsis.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EArjun%20Varain%20Singh%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3EKho%20Gaye%20Hum%20Kahan%3C%2Fem%3E%20tries%20to%20make%20sense%20of%20a%20generation%20that%E2%80%99s%20addicted%20to%20consuming%20other%20people%E2%80%99s%20lives%2C%20and%20how%20they%20slowly%20come%20to%20terms%20with%20the%20lies%20in%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FE1da2YxROaw%3Fsi%3DYqm6kTZTAmGKkQ5j%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%E2%80%99s%20a%20fertile%20premise%20%E2%80%93%20one%20that%20is%20full%20of%20(self)%20deception%2C%20given%20how%20so%20much%20is%20left%20unsaid%20in%20everyday%20life.%20At%20first%20we%20were%20only%20subject%20to%20people%E2%80%99s%20thoughts%20if%20they%20spoke%20to%20us%2C%20but%20now%20they%20reach%20us%20in%20the%20manner%20of%20pictures%2C%20screenshots%2C%20tweets%2C%20threads%2C%20Facebook%20posts.%20Also%2C%20there%E2%80%99s%20a%20way%20for%20us%20to%20actively%20peek%20into%20other%20people%E2%80%99s%20lives%2C%20even%20if%20we%E2%80%99re%20not%20actively%20following%20them.%20Everyone%20wants%20to%20project%20how%20%E2%80%9Chumbled%E2%80%9D%20they%20are%20to%20be%20living%20their%20%E2%80%9Cbest%20lives%E2%80%9D%2C%20but%20it%E2%80%99s%20rarely%20the%20truth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDebutante%20director%20Singh%E2%80%99s%20film%20is%20its%20strongest%20and%20most%20distinct%2C%20when%20it%20depicts%20a%20generation%E2%80%99s%20obsession%20with%20their%20smartphones.%20Our%20entire%20lives%20are%20now%20gamified%20in%20the%20manner%20where%20popularity%20can%20be%20quantified%20through%20a%20dozen%20metrics%3A%20likes%2C%20reactions%2C%20retweets%2C%20followers%2C%20views%2C%20subscribers%2C%20etc.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EKho%20Gaye%20Hum%20Kahan%3C%2Fem%3E%20follows%20three%20friends%20in%20their%2020s%20%E2%80%93%20Imaad%20(Siddhant%20Chaturvedi)%2C%20Ahana%20(Ananya%20Panday)%20and%20Neil%20(Adarsh%20Gourav).%20Imaad%20is%20the%20son%20of%20a%20rich%20businessman%2C%20currently%20pursuing%20his%20dream%20of%20becoming%20a%20stand-up%20comic.%20Neil%2C%20from%20a%20middle-class%20Catholic%20home%2C%20is%20a%20physical%20trainer%20in%20the%20proximity%20of%20Bandra%E2%80%99s%20wealth%20and%20privilege.%20Ahana%20%E2%80%93%20the%20only%20one%20among%20the%20three%20to%20be%20in%20a%20stable%20relationship%20and%20have%20a%20full-time%20job%2C%20comes%20fully%20undone%20when%20her%20boyfriend%20suddenly%20breaks%20up%20with%20her%2C%20without%20giving%20her%20any%20closure%20about%20why%20he%E2%80%99s%20dumping%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%20three%20friends%20are%20dependent%20on%20social%20media%20to%20varying%20degrees.%20Imaad%20needs%20to%20go%20%E2%80%98viral%E2%80%99%20for%20his%20shows%20to%20start%20filling%20up%2C%20Neil%E2%80%99s%20gym%20has%20celebrity%20clients%20like%20Malaika%20Arora%20Khan%20and%20Farhan%20Akhtar%20%E2%80%93%20and%20a%20social%20media%20following%20will%20expedite%20his%20journey%20to%20becoming%20a%20known%20celebrity%20trainer%2C%20and%20open%20his%20own%20gym.%20After%20Ahana%E2%80%99s%20break-up%2C%20she%20gets%20her%20revenge%20by%20curating%20a%20%E2%80%98happy%E2%80%99%20social%20media%20feed%20to%20get%20the%20attention%20of%20her%20ex-boyfriend.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESingh%E2%80%99s%20strong%20observation%20skills%20show%20up%20early%20in%20the%20film%2C%20when%20we%20see%20the%20three%20friends%20sitting%20in%20the%20same%20room%2C%20their%20faces%20lit%20by%20the%20glow%20of%20their%20respective%20phones%2C%20laptops.%20There%20are%20other%20scenes%20too%2C%20where%20Singh%20documents%20his%20characters%E2%80%99%20sudden%20changes%20in%20mood%20after%20a%20bad%20day%2C%20once%20they%20see%20notifications%20on%20their%20posts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%E2%80%99s%20only%20when%20the%20friends%20come%20together%20to%20open%20a%20business%2C%20is%20when%20the%20film%20begins%20to%20take%20the%20convenient%20narrative%20route.%20It%20takes%20only%20a%20few%20questions%20for%20Neil%20to%20convince%20Ahana%20to%20quit%20her%20job%20to%20make%20a%20business%20plan%20for%20his%20gym%2C%20while%20Imaad%20agrees%20to%20invest%20his%20inheritance%20into%20it%20merely%20two%20lines%20later.%20The%20film%E2%80%99s%20primary%20conflict%20%E2%80%93%20the%20confrontation%20between%20Imaad%20and%20Neil%2C%20after%20the%20former%20makes%20some%20unsavoury%20jokes%20on%20the%20latter%E2%80%99s%20relationship%20with%20an%20influencer%2C%20Lala%20(Anya%20Singh)%20%E2%80%93%20appears%20slightly%20underwritten.%20I%20found%20it%20a%20little%20hard%20to%20digest%20that%20a%20stand-up%20comic%20would%20go%20on%20stage%20and%20say%20those%20things%20about%20a%20close%20friend%2C%20especially%20with%20him%20sitting%20in%20the%20audience%2C%20without%20giving%20him%20a%20heads-up%20about%20it.%20Even%20though%20both%20Chaturvedi%20and%20Gourav%20are%20solid%20actors%2C%20who%20do%20their%20best%20to%20sell%20this%20confrontation%20slowly%20escalating%20with%20each%20line%2C%20I%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20help%20but%20think%20how%20the%20scene%20needed%20a%20moment%E2%80%99s%20pause%20before%20it%20to%20make%20it%20truly%20impactful.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20really%20enjoyed%20the%20ease%20between%20Imaad%20and%20Simran%20(Kalki%20Koechlin)%2C%20a%20grieving%20photographer%2C%20who%20meets%20him%20under%20the%20pretext%20of%20a%20project.%20Both%20Chaturvedi%20and%20Koechlin%20are%20secure%20actors%2C%20and%20that%20allows%20them%20to%20truly%20exist%20in%20a%20scene%20without%20any%20off-screen%20baggage.%20Gourav%20is%20a%20very%20fine%20actor%2C%20especially%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20emoting%20with%20body%20language.%20The%20way%20his%20body%20shrinks%2C%20when%20a%20client%20of%20his%20tells%20him%20to%20not%20%E2%80%98cross%20the%20line%E2%80%99%2C%20is%20exemplary.%20Also%2C%20his%20run-ins%20with%20his%20conservative%20father%20(Vijay%20Maurya%2C%20feasting%20on%20these%20tiny%20roles%20in%20Excel%20movies)%2C%20who%20tries%20to%20warn%20him%20about%20his%20boundless%20(and%20sometimes%20reckless)%20ambition.%20It%20might%20not%20be%20saying%20much%20after%20all%2C%20but%20it%E2%80%99s%20abundantly%20clear%20that%20these%20films%20are%20tailor-made%20for%20Panday.%20She%E2%80%99s%20not%20been%20the%20most%20promising%20actor%20around%20since%20she%20made%20her%20debut%20nearly%20five%20years%20ago%2C%20but%20she%20makes%20a%20compelling%20case%20for%20herself%20in%20at%20least%20two%20scenes%20in%20the%20film.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EKho%20Gaye%20Hum%20Kahan%3C%2Fem%3E%20keeps%20us%20on%20the%20hook%20for%20a%20long%20time%2C%20given%20how%20sincere%20and%20easy%20it%20is.%20But%20it%20slowly%20tapers%20off%20towards%20the%20end%20without%20fully%20maximising%20its%20potential.%20A%20track%20around%20Neil%20and%20his%20influencer%20girlfriend%20feels%20tentative%2C%20with%20the%20makers%20trying%20to%20balance%20her%20artifice%2C%20while%20also%20trying%20to%20humanise%20her.%20The%20track%20concludes%20with%20a%20voice-over%20doling%20out%20platitudes%20about%20Neil%E2%80%99s%20bad%20behaviour%2C%20which%20feels%20like%20a%20hurried%2C%20lazy%20way%20to%20wrap%20things%20up.%20There%E2%80%99s%20a%20scene%20towards%20the%20end%20when%20Imaad%20owns%20up%20to%20his%20demons%20from%20the%20past%20by%20announcing%20it%20in%20his%20set%20to%20an%20audience.%20It%20feels%20awkwardly%20written%2C%20and%20performed%20by%20an%20unusually%20stiff%20Chaturvedi%2C%20given%20how%20he%E2%80%99s%20free-flowing%20in%20most%20other%20scenes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EArjun%20Varain%20Singh%E2%80%99s%20film%20is%20the%20rare%20Hindi%20film%20that%20seems%20to%20understand%20the%20lies%20of%20social%20media%2C%20but%20unfortunately%20chooses%20to%20not%20cut%20too%20deep.%20While%20it%20results%20in%20a%20respectable%2C%20watchable%20debut%2C%20it%20never%20quite%20ascends%20to%20becoming%20a%20document%20of%20a%20whole%20generation.%20It%E2%80%99s%20ultimately%20sad%20that%20for%20its%20commentary%20on%20social%20media%2C%20%3Cem%3EKho%20Gaye%20Hum%20Kahan%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20the%20recall%20value%20of%20an%20Insta%20reel.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703658892000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F27120951%2Fimage-1675.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Fkho-gaye-hum-kahan-starts-strong-but-settles-with-the-recall-value-of-an-insta-reel%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22One%20more%20film%20about%20the%20coming%20of%20age%20of%20three%20friends%2C%20this%20time%20in%20the%20era%20of%20social%20media%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Fkho-gaye-hum-kahan-starts-strong-but-settles-with-the-recall-value-of-an-insta-reel%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Project%20Cheetah%3A%20Male%20Cheetah%20Agni%20That%20Ventured%20Into%20Rajasthan%20Tranquilised%20and%20%E2%80%98Brought%20Back%E2%80%99%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2F27113722%2Farmand-kamffer-mhbXY-RcLZA-unsplash.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EBengaluru%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3E%20After%20around%20three%20months%20of%20being%20confined%20to%20enclosures%20in%20Madhya%20Pradesh%E2%80%99s%20Kuno%20National%20Park%2C%20four%20cheetahs%20were%20released%20back%20into%20the%20wild%20starting%20December%2017.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspa